{"title_page": "Sabumon Abdusamad", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian actor and television presenter}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}}\n{{notability|Biographies|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Sabumon Abdusamad\n| image              = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = Sabumon Abdusamad\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=y|1979|10|16}}\n| birth_place        = [[Kayamkulam]], [[Kerala]], [[India]]\n| alma_mater         = [[University College, Trivandrum]]\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Actor|Television Anchor}}\n| years_active       = 2000\u2013present\n| height_m           = 1.85\n| spouse             = Sneha Bhaskaran<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/malayalam/himas-strategies-against-sabu-have-turned-vulgar-sneha-bhaskaran-wife-of-bigg-boss-malayalam-finalist-sabumon/articleshow/65968804.cms |title=Hima's strategies against Sabu have turned vulgar: Sneha Bhaskaran, wife of Bigg Boss Malayalam finalist Sabumon|last=Nair|first=Radhika|work= Times Of India |access-date=2018-10-20}}</ref>\n| footnotes          = \n| awards             = \n}}\n\n'''Sabumon Abdusamad''' (born 16 October 1979), also known [[Mononymous person|mononymously]] as '''Sabu''', is an Indian [[actor]] and [[television presenter]] who works in [[Malayalam cinema]]. He was the winner of the [[Bigg Boss (Malayalam season 1)|first season]] of ''[[Bigg Boss (Malayalam TV series)|Bigg Boss]]''.\n\n==Personal life==\nSabu hails from [[Kayamkulam]], [[Alappuzha]]. He holds three graduation degrees, in Malayalam,  Journalism and in Law respectively from [[University College, Trivandrum]]. He initially worked in the sales and operations division of [[Lufthansa|Lufthansa Airlines]] in Saudi Arabia. He later quit the job and decided to pursue his passion in acting. He is the Chief executive officer of SAB productions company. He is married and has two daughters. He is the Chief Executive Officer at SAB productions.\n\n==Career==\nSabu initially achieved success through the TV show ''Tharikida'', which focused on pranks on unsuspecting people. Due to the success of the show, people started addressing him as Tharikida Sabu.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/radio-and-tv/quick-five-sabumon-the-name-of-the-game/article5557398.ece |title= Quick Five: Sabumon -The name of the game\u2026|last=M|first=Athira|work= The Hindu|access-date=2018-10-20}}</ref> Sabu continued to do television shows, and his role as an interviewer in the TV show ''[[Midukki]]'' was widely appreciated.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://starsunfolded.com/sabumon-abdusamad/ |title=Sabumon Abdusamad Height, Weight, Age, Wife, Biography & More |work= Starsunfolded.com |access-date=2018-10-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://english.manoramaonline.com/entertainment/entertainment-news/2018/09/30/sabumon-midukki-video-viral-reba-monica-interview.html |title=Throwback: Sabumon video from 'Midukki' is trending!...|work= Manorama Online |access-date=2018-10-18}}</ref>\n\nSabu was the thirteenth contestant in ''Bigg Boss'', a show hosted by Malayalam actor [[Mohanlal]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://newsable.asianetnews.com/entertainment/good-news-superstar-mohanlal-to-host-bigg-boss-malayalam-p7fdth |title=Good news: Superstar Mohanlal to host Bigg Boss Malayalam |last=Barua|first=Richa|work=Asianet Newsable |access-date=2018-10-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/television/mohanlal-bigg-boss-malayalam-contestants-list-asianet-5230422/ |title=Bigg Boss Malayalam: These celebrities may enter Mohanlal\u2019s show |last=Web Desk|first=Express |work=The Indian Express |access-date=2018-10-17}}</ref> He lasted the entire duration of the 98-day show and went on to win the title, beating competition from [[Pearle Maaney]], Shiyas Kareem, [[Srinish Aravind]] and [[Aristo Suresh]] in the grand finale.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/malayalam/bigg-boss-malayalam-winner-sabumon-abdusamad-bags-the-trophy/articleshow/66020183.cms |title=Bigg Boss Malayalam winner: Sabumon Abdusamad lifts the trophy - Times of India |work=The Times of India |access-date=2018-10-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/bigg-boss-malayalam-grand-finale-live-updates-mohanlal-reveal-name-winner-today-781910 |title=Bigg Boss Malayalam grand finale live updates: Sabumon wins the prestigious title |last=Narayanan |first=Nirmal |work=International Business Times, India Edition |access-date=2018-10-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/videos/tv/malayalam/sabumon-abdusamad-to-gayathri-arun-top-newsmakers-of-2018/videoshow/67229944.cms |title=Sabumon Abdusamad to Gayathri Arun: Top Newsmakers of 2018 |work=The Times of India |access-date=2018-12-25}}</ref>\n\nSabu also owns a production company, SAB Productions.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.tofler.in/sab-productions-private-limited/company/U74300KL2013PTC034471 |title=SAB PRODUCTIONS PRIVATE LIMITED |work=Tofler.in |access-date=2018-10-18}}</ref>\n\n==Television==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Program\n! Channel\n! Role\n|-\n|2000||''Tharikida<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/malayalam/Tharikida-sabu-is-on-a-roll-/articleshow/26679479.cms |title= Tharikida sabu is on a roll !|last=Pillai|first=Radhika C|work= Times of India|access-date=2018-10-20}}</ref>''||[[Surya TV]]||Host\n|-\n|2005||''Attahasam<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/what-is-the-good-word/article3192956.ece |title= What is the good word? |date=20 May 2006 | newspaper=The Hindu|access-date=20 October 2018}}</ref>''||[[Asianet Plus]]||Host\n|-\n|2013||''[[Midukki]]''||[[Mazhavil Manorama]]||Guest judge\n|-\n|2014||''Take It Easy<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.mazhavilmanorama.com/shows/non-fiction/take-it