ll|footballer]] who plays for [[Matlock Town F.C.|Matlock Town]], on loan from [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]], as a [[midfielder]].\n\n==Career==\nGoldthorp made his debut for [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]] on 25 September 2018 in the [[EFL Trophy]] in a 1-1 draw against Everton U21s,<ref name = \"2018-19\"/> scoring the winning penalty.<ref name = \"penalty\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thetelegraphandargus.co.uk/sport/16902726.bradford-city-goldthorp-fires-winning-penalty/|title=Bradford City: Goldthorp fires winning penalty|date=26 September 2018|accessdate=26 September 2018|author=Simon Parker|publisher=Telegraph & Argus}}</ref> On 9 October 2018, manager [[David Hopkin]] stated that Goldthorp would make his first senior start, also in the EFL Trophy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thetelegraphandargus.co.uk/sport/16969465.bradford-city-teenagers-checkatrade-chance/|title=Bradford City: Teenager's Checkatrade chance|date=9 October 2018|accessdate=9 October 2018|author=Simon Parker|publisher=Telegraph & Argus}}</ref> He was praised by Hopkin for his performance in the match, which was a 4\u20131 home defeat.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thetelegraphandargus.co.uk/sport/16971932.hopkin-impressed-with-teenage-duo-in-bantams-loss/|title=Hopkin impressed with teenage duo in Bantams loss|date=10 October 2018|accessdate=10 October 2018|author=Simon Parker|publisher=Telegraph & Argus}}</ref>\n\nOn 1 October 2019 he moved on loan to [[Mossley A.F.C.|Mossley]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/officialbantams/status/1179056175108825092|title=NEWS &#124; @EliotGoldthorp1 has joined @MossleyAFC on a one-month work experience loan. #BCAFC &#124; #OurCity|first=Bradford|last=City|date=1 October 2019}}</ref> He scored 3 goals in 5 games before being recalled by Bradford City later that month.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mossleycorrespondent.co.uk/?p=7711|title=Eliot\u2019s gone, but not forgotten at Seel Park|first=Tony|last=Bugby|date=25 October 2019}}</ref> His 5 games for Mossley included 3 in the league, 1 in the Manchester Premier Cup, and 1 in the FA Trophy Preliminary Round where he scored a hat-trick.<ref name = \"Mossley\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.mossleyafc.club/team/fixtures-results/mossleyafc-vs-widnes-2-2/|title=Mossley AFC &#124; Mossley AFC vs Widnes}}<br>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mossleyafc.club/team/fixtures-results/marine-vs-mossleyafc/|title=Mossley AFC &#124; Marine vs Mossley AFC}}<br>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mossleyafc.club/team/fixtures-results/mossleyafc-vs-abbey-hey-fc/|title=Mossley AFC &#124; Mossley AFC vs Abbey Hey FC}}<br>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mossleyafc.club/team/fixtures-results/cleethorpes-town-vs-mossleyafc/|title=Mossley AFC &#124; Cleethorpes Town vs Mossley AFC}}<br>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mossleyafc.club/team/fixtures-results/city-of-liverpool-vs-mossley-afc/|title=Mossley AFC &#124; City of Liverpool vs Mossley AFC}}</ref>\n\nHe moved on loan to [[Radcliffe F.C.|Radcliffe]] in December 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/officialbantams/status/1209504002955722758|title=NEWS &#124; Eliot Goldthorp has joined @radcliffeboro on a short-term work experience loan|first=Bradford City|last=AFC|date=24 December 2019}}</ref> On 8 January 2020 the loan deal was ended early.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thetelegraphandargus.co.uk/sport/18146729.bradford-park-avenue-lose-youngsters-early-loan-endings/|title=City recall youngster early from Avenue loan|website=Bradford Telegraph and Argus}}</ref> In February 2020 he moved on loan to [[Matlock Town F.C.|Matlock Town]] until the end of the season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.matlocktownfc.co.uk/gladiators-add-bradford-citys-goldthorp-on-loan.asp|title=Gladiators add Bradford City's Goldthorp on loan|website=www.matlocktownfc.co.uk}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|20 November 2019}}\n\n{| class=wikitable style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspa